722336f-a.text:
760 Park Avenue, at N.W. corner of Third Street, nearing completion. It replaces two small 4-story houses facing on 72nd Street. At N.W.corner of 72nd Street we have a glimpse of Sunnyside, which will be demolished in September, 1929.
Notice old fashioned stop-and-go signal in the center of the intersection.
March, 18, 1921.
Photograph by Sterrett Brothers, Inc, Builders.
Gift of E.M. Jenks.

Neg # 1239
Net # 1380 A

722335f-a.text:
755 Psrk Avenue, at S. E. corner of 72nd Street, seen from N. W. corner, apartment building built about 1913. Note parks in center of the avenue being narrowed and remodelled. This work has not yet begun above 72nd Street.
Early 1929.
Capital Photo Service.
